reviews.text: The broth was too salty and oily. Also, the pork was dry and bland. Only the homemade noodles lived up to expectations.

A very popular dipping noodle restaurant in busy Tsim Sha Tsui. Expect to fall in line each time. Despite the wait, service was quick. Presentation was mundane but flavours of their dipping noodle sauce was good. 

***cash only***
Nice dipping noodles. A good place to have your ramen alone
Best value and taste good

Reasonably priced Japanese ramen/tsuekemen ( dipping noodles) on the outside of K11 mall.
Had their spicy dipping noodles for $80.  You can choose small, medium, large noodles-140gm, 210 g, 240gm  size, same price.
I chose large which was not really that big a portion.  Noodles was quite good, al dente. Few bamboo slices, slice of pork chau siu and a lump of pork belly, soft egg, seaweed, green onions.  Standard tsuekemen.  Dip in thick and just slightly spicy soup.  At the end you can ask waitstaffs to bring you a pot of hot broth in a thermos to dilute the broth, turn it into soup.
Service was super fast and efficient.
CASH only.

reviews.text:
簡單好吃的日本麵店，
主打沾麵，
但我點了季節限定的
明太子奶油拌麵。

明太子充滿了整碗麵，
味道很夠！
配料有牛油，蔥花，紫菜碎及幾粒叉燒😌
好好吃，拌餐自海帶湯正正常常。

另外還點了黑椒雞翼，
炸過的雞翼沾上了甜甜的日式醬汁，
還洒上足量的黑椒碎，
香口惹味，作為麵的點綴不錯👌🏻

餐廳選擇不算很多，
簡單一餐的話可以考慮一下！

留意暫時只收現金🙆🏻‍♀️

日本頗負盛名的麫所，而尖沙咀河内道的是香港首間分店。麫條與日本相比則有明顯差距，就算舆剛在泰國芭堤雅新張的分店相比亦高下立見，未知是與原材料有關否？义燒亦覺味道與肉質亦覺有雲坭之别！撈麪的湯（？）底頗為夠味（鹹？），唯一可取的是隨麫伴上的温泉蛋，糖沁而很有蛋味。餃子亦煎得不錯，做到金黄色的外層及香口，而沒有過火焦燶的出現，可見師傅是很用心的。店面陳設簡單而整潔，照明十分和熙，令人舒服；侍應服務亦中規中矩，一般反應都很快，整體還可以。性價比不高，且不值得長時間去排隊輪候進食，可能亦是國内同胞為盛名而來吧！
獨自的晚餐，快而飽，一人路過可以考慮，坐在bar枱氣氛也不錯
限定山椒拉麵，口味不錯，值得一試。 煎餃子與拉麵是絕配。

山椒拉麵(中)，湯濃，麵夠蛋香，山椒夠刺激，
唔係度度都有山椒拉麵食，不過就油左少少

reviews.text: Smaller mall in Tsim Sha Tsui, specialising more on smaller boutique stores. The mall also has a nice, artsy outdoor area on the ground floor. Overall you probably won't be staying here for very long, but the visit can be pleasant. There will likely be a lot more to do around here as the bigger extension to K11 opens later this year.
The mall is undergoing renovation but you can still find lots of good restaurants and shops there. It is convenient where you can connect to MTR station.
Very good location with many shops. Always visit here. Some restaurant is great. Love Empire duck./ ice cream shop.

Great mall if you want to see something different! Always has different art exhibits going on. Also has a lot of designer and boutique stores along with the usual ones at a variety of price ranges. Love it!
Very clean and new shopping mall, connected to a hotel and very close to MTR station. Good dining choices offered (not chained restaurants), there is a grocery store too.
